Started to make tagging for multiple models using polymorphic approach:

## TODO From Scrach -
-------------------------

1. Create Tags model 

rails g model tag name

class Tag < ActiveRecord::Base
  attr_accessible :name
  has_many :taggings
   
end


2.Create common tagging model

rails g model tagging taggable_id:integer taggable_type:string user_id:integer tag_id:intege

class Tagging < ActiveRecord::Base
  attr_accessible :tag_id, :taggable_id, :taggable_type, :user_id

  belongs_to :tag
  belongs_to :taggable, polymorphic: true

end


3. Add common functionality to other models:

has_many :taggings, as: :taggable, :dependent => :destroy

rake db:migrate 


--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Reverse oprations:

From above migration created two tables so rollback twice.

rake db:rollback

rake db:rollback

then . 

rails d model tag name

rails d model tagging taggable_id:integer taggable_type:string user_id:integer tag_id:integer



